<subSubSection pageNumber="506" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="506">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="506">Note:</emphasis>
Krukoff (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="506">Phytologia</emphasis>
22: 250. 1971) noted seeing 888.5 (LINN) and added &quot;it is clear that this name is correctly interpreted&quot; but this falls short of a formal typification. In any case, this material has the annotation &quot;
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Erythrina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Erythrina</taxonomicName>
crista 93&quot; - the 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“93”">&quot;93&quot;</normalizedToken>
corresponding with the number cited in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="506">
<volumeTitle>Plantae Surinamenses</volumeTitle>
</emphasis>
: 12 (1775), making it a post-1767 addition to the herbarium. Krukoff &amp; Barneby (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="506">Lloydia</emphasis>
37: 343. 1974) noted the existence of 888.4 (LINN), but did not indicate it as the type.
</paragraph>
